    <dashboard name='Story 1' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#c2c0b6' fontname='Anthropic Sans,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Segoe UI,sans-serif' fontsize='16'>Cybersecurity Threat Analysis — Data Story (2015–2024)</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='1038' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97766' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98698' x='651' y='1117'>
            <zone h='3911' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98698' x='651' y='1117' />
            <zone fixed-size='149' h='20810' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98698' x='651' y='5028' />
            <zone h='73045' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98698' x='651' y='25838'>
              <flipboard active-id='1' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='In 2015, the average cyberattack scored justIn 2015, the average cyberattack severity was just 0.22 out of 15. By 2024, it climbed to 6.86 — a 30-fold rise in under a decade. The trend line is not an estimate — it is a linear regression with R² = 0.87, meaning this rise is 87% mathematically predictable.&#10;&#10;▸ Severity 2015 → 0.22 / 15 — barely detectable&#10;▸ Severity 2024 → 6.86 / 15 — major damage level&#10;▸ Severity 2023 → 7.00 / 15 — peak recorded year&#10;▸ Regression R² = 0.87 — statistically proven, not coincidence&#10;▸ Forecast → severity reaching 9 by 2027 if trend continues&#10;▸ Critical attacks → rising fast since 2020&#10;▸ Low severity → stayed flat — not just more noise 0.22 out of 15 on the severity scale. By 2024 that number reached 6.86 — a 30-fold increase in under ten years. The trend lines on this chart make the direction impossible to ignore. Critical and High severity attacks have been climbing steadily while low-level attacks stayed flat. This is not more noise — it is a genuine escalation. For organisations that have not revisited their security strategy since 2020, this chart shows exactly how much the threat has changed.' captured-sheet='Jinesh - Trend Over Time.' id='1' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{B4F73791-2D9E-4E1A-8367-A4ED702F3A83}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard name='Story 2' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Volume and Severity Rise Together</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='1047' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97766' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98698' x='651' y='1117'>
            <zone h='4330' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98698' x='651' y='1117' />
            <zone fixed-size='172' h='24022' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98698' x='651' y='5447' />
            <zone h='69414' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98698' x='651' y='29469'>
              <flipboard active-id='1' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='Most people assume more attacks means When attack volume rises, severity rises with it — every single year without exception. This scatter plot was built using a real Python regression model through Tabpy, not a basic estimate. Each dot is one year. The direction from bottom-left to top-right tells the whole story.&#10;&#10;▸ 2015 → 131 attacks — severity 0.22 — safe zone&#10;▸ 2020 → 71 attacks — severity 3.42 — first major jump&#10;▸ 2022 → 354 attacks — severity 6.03 — crossed critical threshold&#10;▸ 2023 → 723 attacks — severity 7.00 — worst year on record&#10;▸ Regression R² = 0.73 — 73% of severity explained by volume alone&#10;▸ Method → Python LinearRegression via Tabpy — real statistical model&#10;▸ Critical line → score 6 = disruption and large-scale data lossmore low-level noise. This chart proves otherwise. Each dot is one year — further right means more attacks, higher up means more severe. The dots go from the bottom-left corner in 2015 to the top-right corner in 2023. More attacks and worse attacks, always together. The Python regression model built using Tabpy gives an R² of 0.73 — meaning 73% of the change in severity can be explained simply by knowing how many attacks happened that year. A security team sized only on incident volume will always be underprepared in the worst years.' captured-sheet='Jinesh - Linear Regression via Tabpy.' id='1'>
                    <currentDeltas>
                      <worksheet name='Jinesh - Linear Regression via Tabpy.'>
                        <style delta-type='added'>
                          <style-rule element='axis'>
                            <encoding attr='space' class='0' field='[federated.0mk0h0s18oe37v17i3vez07tqkuy].[avg:impact_indicator_score:qk]' field-type='quantitative' max='10.293196459601912' min='-1.8845124779866556' range-type='fixed' scope='rows' type='space' />
                            <encoding attr='space' class='0' field='[federated.0mk0h0s18oe37v17i3vez07tqkuy].[usr:Calculation_1866210306007065:qk]' field-type='quantitative' fold='true' max='10.293196459601912' min='-1.8845124779866556' range-type='fixed' scope='rows' synchronized='true' type='space' />
                            <encoding attr='space' class='0' field='[federated.0mk0h0s18oe37v17i3vez07tqkuy].[none:Calculation_1866210305056791:qk]' field-type='quantitative' max='1157' min='-58' range-type='fixed' scope='cols' type='space' />
                          </style-rule>
                        </style>
                      </worksheet>
                    </currentDeltas>
                    <capturedDeltas />
                  </story-point>
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{B92E6688-321E-417B-8B4E-D457E8F5C984}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard name='Story 3' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Top Initiator Countries</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='1022' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97766' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98698' x='651' y='1117'>
            <zone h='4330' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98698' x='651' y='1117' />
            <zone fixed-size='146' h='20391' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98698' x='651' y='5447' />
            <zone h='73045' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98698' x='651' y='25838'>
              <flipboard active-id='1' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='The top attackers are not individuals sitting in basements — they are governments. Russia, China, North Korea and Iran lead the initiator list year after year, funded by state budgets and driven by geopolitical strategy. This is what explains why severity keeps rising — the attackers have unlimited resources.&#10;&#10;▸ Top 4 initiators → Russia, China, North Korea, Iran&#10;▸ Actor type → state-sponsored — not criminal organisations&#10;▸ Motivation → intelligence gathering, political disruption, economic damage&#10;▸ Resources → military-grade funding — far beyond criminal capability&#10;▸ Pattern → same countries appear every year — consistent, not random&#10;▸ Link to Story 1 → state actors drive severity rise&#10;▸ Link to Story 2 → organised campaigns = high volume AND high severity' captured-sheet='Jinesh - Top Initiator Countries.' id='1' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{D0F22B9F-5BE1-47EF-9084-C3BC66E85FB7}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard name='Story 4' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Top Receiver Countries</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='1147' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97766' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98698' x='651' y='1117'>
            <zone h='4330' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98698' x='651' y='1117' />
            <zone fixed-size='141' h='19693' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98698' x='651' y='5447' />
            <zone h='73743' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98698' x='651' y='25140'>
              <flipboard active-id='1' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='Being targeted is not random — it is a deliberate choice made by sophisticated attackers. Ukraine, the United States, Germany and the UK absorb a disproportionate share of all recorded attacks because they hold the most valuable data, infrastructure and geopolitical importance in the world.&#10;&#10;▸ Top 4 targets → Ukraine, USA, Germany, United Kingdom&#10;▸ Ukraine → active conflict — direct military and political targeting&#10;▸ USA, Germany, UK → economic power + intelligence value + NATO membership&#10;▸ Pattern → highly concentrated — few countries absorb most attacks&#10;▸ Selection → deliberate, strategic — not opportunistic&#10;▸ Link to Story 3 → state actors choose high-value targets on purpose&#10;▸ Geography matters → Europe and USA face highest baseline risk globally' captured-sheet='Jinesh - Top Receiver Countries.' id='1' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{A1E7B3C2-255C-489C-8428-F4C260145621}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard name='Story 5' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Attack Categories</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='1089' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97766' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98698' x='651' y='1117'>
            <zone h='4330' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98698' x='651' y='1117' />
            <zone fixed-size='189' h='26397' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98698' x='651' y='5447' />
            <zone h='67039' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98698' x='651' y='31844'>
              <flipboard active-id='1' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='For years, data theft dominated — steal quietly, leave no trace. But since 2020, disruption attacks have been climbing fast. Disruption does not try to be invisible. It shuts systems down, takes services offline, and causes damage that is immediate and public. The threat is no longer just about losing data — it is about losing the ability to operate.&#10;&#10;▸ Data theft → dominant attack type — quiet, profitable, hard to detect&#10;▸ Disruption → rising sharply since 2020 — visible, immediate, operational&#10;▸ Key difference → theft hides | disruption announces itself&#10;▸ 2022–2024 → disruption closing the gap on data theft rapidly&#10;▸ Signal → attackers confident enough to cause visible harm — alarming shift&#10;▸ Link to Story 3 → state actors prefer disruption for geopolitical impact&#10;▸ Link to Story 1 → disruption attacks push severity scores higher' captured-sheet='Jinesh - Attack Categories.' id='1' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{37286AA2-51BB-4FD1-A5F4-A085516E89FE}' />
    </dashboard>
  </dashboards>
